txt.en: 'Come, my friends... hooom, let us put their violence to an end and push them from these woods!'
'You lot, hold them back! I'll warn Voskor and the others!'
'You cursed trees! Leave me be or I'll burn you to the ground!'
'Stay back! Back!'
'Hey! Who's that there?'
'No... you?! I remember you!'
'The Uruk is dead and the Orcs will trouble us no more, [placeholder]! Come, let us leave this place....'
'You were there when that tree threw me into the woods, whelp!'
Instance: Forest for the Trees
'You stole that tasty Man-flesh right out of my hands!'
'So you call on your precious trees to save you again, then?'
'This time you won't be so lucky... my flames will sear you and your friends to ashes!'
'And after I feast on what remains of you, I will cut and burn every last tree and spite this miserable forest!'
'ENOUGH!'
'Hoom... broom. These Orcs have cut our brethren down and laid waste to our forest.'
'What?! Voskor won't like this....'
'Burn! Burn! I won't leave one tree standing!'
'Curse you... even with my death, your winter will NEVER end!'
'We Ents must march against them, lest they take everything that remains....'
'Too many trees! Run!'
'Their camp will return to the earth through our helping, but they cannot hew another tree amidst our indecision.'
